CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 12, 1957, page A15, reads: "Fascinating Models - Gladys Grimball and Gloria Grate of Pittsburgh showed wardrobes of fascinating glamor. Gladys Grimball is wearing a pair of shoes whose price was a mere $100.00! 'Twas the heel interest that counted. Gloria Grate makes a picture in a formal gown of elegant simplicity."
TitMainTitle: Two women, Gladys Grimball and Gloria Golden Grate, modeling evening dresses, gloves, and fur stoles, at fashion show for the Pittsburgh National Council of Negro Women
